Combining these effects, the adjustments are +100 (for ketone), +50 (for NH group), and +5 (for methyl group) to the base melting point of pyridine.

Revising the ketone group influence to +120 degrees Celsius and the NH group influence to +70 degrees Celsius offers a closer approximation.
